{
  "text": ". If f \u2208 S \u2212 then the action (8) and decomposition [CITATION_1] imply that for all i \u2208 {0} \u222a (V \\ V leaves ) we have [\u03c0f ](i) = f (i) = \u2212f (i), i.e. f (i) = 0. Therefore if f \u2208 S \u2212 (it is only non-zero on V leaves ) is an eigenvector of L(G 1 ) with eigenvalue \u03bb it is also an eigenvector of L(G 2 ) with the same eigenvalue and hence \u03c3 \u2212 (G 1 ) = \u03c3 \u2212 (G 2 ). The same reasoning gives us that",
